🧾 Terraform Configuration
🔹 EBS Volume Creation
resource "aws_ebs_volume" "k8s_volume" {
  availability_zone = "us-east-1a"
  size              = 5
  type              = "gp2"

  tags = {
    Name = "devops-vol"
  }
}
🔹 EBS Snapshot Creation
resource "aws_ebs_snapshot" "devops_snapshot" {
  volume_id   = aws_ebs_volume.k8s_volume.id
  description = "Devops Snapshot"

  tags = {
    Name = "devops-vol-ss"
  }
}
🔗 Key Concepts Applied
1. Infrastructure as Code (IaC)

All infrastructure is defined in code using Terraform, making it:

Repeatable
Version-controlled
Easy to maintain
2. Dependency Management

Terraform automatically understands resource dependencies:

EBS Volume → Snapshot

No manual ordering required.

3. Tagging Strategy

Tags were used for resource identification:

Name: devops-vol
Snapshot Name: devops-vol-ss

This improves:

Cost tracking
Resource identification
Governance
🚀 Deployment Steps
1. Initialize Terraform
terraform init
2. Validate configuration
terraform validate
3. Apply infrastructure
terraform apply -auto-approve
🔍 Verification Steps

Check snapshot status using AWS CLI:

aws ec2 describe-snapshots \
--owner-ids self \
--region us-east-1

Ensure:

Snapshot name: devops-vol-ss
Description: Devops Snapshot
State: completed
